function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes two arguments: a timestamp of type `DateTime`, and an integer `bump`. The function adds `bump` hours to the `DateTime` object and returns the result. If `bump` is not provided, it defaults to +3 hours. If the input `dt` is not of type `DateTime`, the function will throw a method error.
